                            "type": "faq",
                            "heading": "Questions and Answers",
                            "items": [
                                {
                                    "question": "How do I install Folio Studio?",
                                    "answer": "Folio Studio is distributed as a Docker image. Pull it with <code>docker pull ghcr.io/jmjuanes/folio-studio</code> and follow the setup instructions in the documentation."
                                },
                                {
                                    "question": "What are the server requirements?",
                                    "answer": "Folio Studio is lightweight and runs on any machine that supports Docker — including a Raspberry Pi, a personal laptop, or a VPS. No special hardware is required."
                                },
                                {
                                    "question": "Can I migrate my boards from Folio Lite?",
                                    "answer": "Yes. You can export your board from Folio Lite and import it directly into Folio Studio. The format is fully compatible between both versions."
                                },
                                {
                                    "question": "Is Folio Studio also free?",
                                    "answer": "Yes. Folio Studio is free and open source, just like Folio Lite. You only pay for the infrastructure you choose to run it on."
                                },
                                {
                                    "question": "Can multiple people use the same Folio Studio instance?",
                                    "answer": "Folio Studio is currently designed as a personal or small-team tool. Multi-user collaboration with real-time sync is not yet supported, but it's on the roadmap."
                                }
